Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Chop the @baking potato{1} into 3cm chunks (no need to peel). Pop onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{2%tbsp}, season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}, sprinkle over the @mixed herbs{1%sachet}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf for ~{20%minutes} - you'll roast them for longer once you've crushed them.

Meanwhile, halve the @premium tomato mix{190%g}. Tear the @ciabatta{1} into roughly 2cm chunks. Drain the @burrata{125%g}.

Heat a small #frying pan{} on medium heat (no oil). Once hot, add the @pine nuts{15%g} and dry-fry, stirring regularly, until lightly toasted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> Watch them like a hawk as they can burn easily.

Transfer to a small #bowl{} and set aside. In a large bowl, combine the @pesto{32%g} and @olive oil{}. Set your dressing aside.

Pop the ciabatta onto another medium baking tray in a single layer. Drizzle with oil, season with salt and pepper, sprinkle over the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g}, then toss to coat.

Bake the croutons on the middle shelf until golden, ~{8-10%minutes}, then remove from the oven and set aside.

When the potatoes have cooked for 20 mins, remove them from the oven. Use the bottom of a bowl or pan to lightly crush each potato. Drizzle the smashed potatoes with more oil, and return to the top shelf of your oven until crispy and golden, ~{10-15%minutes}.

When everything's ready, add the smashed potatoes, cheesy croutons, tomatoes and @wild rocket{40%g} to the bowl of pesto dressing. Toss to coat. Season with salt and pepper.

Share your ultimate Italian inspired salad between your #bowls{}. Tear the burrata in half and place on top. Sprinkle over the toasted pine nuts and drizzle over the @balsamic glaze{12%ml} to finish. Enjoy!